## DatePositionParser.next() method

Parse date as string and returns information about position and selected part of date, while moving it to next part, if it was last part returns null

<b>Signature:</b>

```typescript
next(date: string, cursorPosition: number): null | DatePositionParserResult;
```

## Parameters

|  Parameter | Type | Description |
|  --- | --- | --- |
|  date | string | String date to be parsed |
|  cursorPosition | number | Current cursor position |

<b>Returns:</b>

null \| [DatePositionParserResult](./datetime.datepositionparserresult.md)
